CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 16, 1958, pg. B2 reads: "Bloch Party - A kiddie block party was given in the yard of Mrs. Della Walker of 235 Carron St., recently. The kiddies were served hot dogs, pop, potato chips, ice cream and cake.  Included in the festivities were various games, songs and a "slop" contest.  A musical treat was given by the Five Arabs who entertained the children. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of boys, including one wearing suspenders and bow tie, and girls, posed on pavement for block party on Carron Street
